    "last_activity_date" : 1487846758,
    "creation_date" : 1487846758,
    "answer_id" : 42413501,
    "question_id" : 9445196,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're using eclipse, there's a setting that inserts escape chars automatically when pasting:</p>\n\n<p>Window -> Preferences -> Java -> Editor -> Typing -> In String Literals -> Escape text when pasting into a string literal </p>\n\n<p>Then, when something like <code>D:\\Env\\Images\\image1.png</code> is in your clipboard and you paste it into eclipse, it'll automatically look like this: <code>D:\\\\Env\\\\Images\\\\image1.png</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
